  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Top and Bottom",
      "body": "Cut tops and bottoms to length.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/08ae9a2977008f45.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Details top and bottom",
      "body": "We wanted to round the bottoms and cut a cove on the tops. Using a roll of tape as a guide we traced the radius on the tops and bottoms and cut with a Jig saw",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/1f7b227474544595.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Sanding Corners",
      "body": "Use an Oscillating sander to clean up the cuts.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/643bf9c299bcfae8.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cut the sides",
      "body": "We cut the sides using the miter saw at a 5° angle on both ends and laid them out so the bottom of the side is 3\" from the edge and the tops are 6\" from the edge",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/cd12531b19722061.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Drilling Pocket Holes",
      "body": "Drill pocket holes to attach the top and bottom to the sides\n\n**Tip:** Water drainage Drill the pocket holes so they are facing down, this will allow them to shed any water.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/244c187028ee96f5.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Side assembly",
      "body": "Assemble the sides using 2 1/2 Blue-Kote screws, then measure the middle bracing 18\" from the bottom of the side-bottom. mark (28 3/4\"), cut, pocket hole and install.\n\n**Tip:** This middle brace should be the height of the garden bed.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/a4f6b08c0b1f99d7.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "welded wire fencing",
      "body": "Attach welded wire fencing to the inside of both sides using fence staples. Cut excess fencing with diagonal cutters (we went from the middle brace up)",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/2104a2cc4ef28aaa.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assemble",
      "body": "We ripped a 2x6 in half for the braces to connect the two halves. We used deck screws to assemble the 2 sides to the rails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/2bc8ee5971831f41.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Rollerhooks",
      "body": "Install roller hooks and use trellis clips to train your tomato plant up the line.\n\n**Tip:** I used the same fence staples to install the roller hooks. If I had to do it again I would run a wire from one side of the trellis to the other and hang them from that.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/8ba10c96a536ee81.webp"
    }
  ],
